abstract: Bill Belichick has been an assistant coach in the National Football League for six years, having joined the Baltimore Colts after graduating from Wesleyan in 1975. He moved on to Detroit in 1976 and Denver in 1978 before taking over the special teams for the Giants last season. He is only 28 years old.

MIAMI, Oct. 24--When Capt. Manuel J. (Pete) Fernandez Jr., the Korean War fighter ace, came home to Miami in 1953, thousands turned out for the Memorial Day Parade to greet the "modest little pilot." His mother cried and blonde beauty queens perched on his knees.

abstract: MORGANTOWN, W.Va., Oct. 25, (AP)--Curt Warner returned a kickoff 88 yards, his second touchdown of the game, and helped Penn State gain a 20-15 victory over West Virginia, its 22d in a row over the Mountaineers.

abstract: IN my wallet, I carry a slightly faded ticket to the first game of the 1964 World Series in  Philadelphia. I never got to use it, of course, because the Phillies managed to squander a sixand-a-half-game lead with 12 to play and finish in an ignominious tie for second.

abstract: UNIONDALE, L.I., Oct. 25--Still trying to make up for the indignities they suffered last May in losing to the New York Islanders in the Stanley Cup final, the Philadelphia Flyers posted their second triumph in three days over the National Hockey League champions tonight.

abstract: George Steinbrenner, who has said the anti-Yankee conspiracy he suspects prompted him to pursue a trade for Dave Winfield, is not alone in that suspicion. Al Frohman, Winfield's agent, said the other day he had heard such rumors and now Richard Moss, Winfield's lawyer, has voiced his concern.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 23--In their first official confrontation since the final round of the Stanley Cup playoffs last spring, the Philadelphia Flyers achieved a modicum of revenge tonight by defeating the New York Islanders, 4-2, at the Spectrum.
